  "prompt": "What is the status of net neutrality in all countries?",
  "response": "Net neutrality status varies widely across different countries:\n\nUnited States:\n- Repealed in 2017 by FCC\n- Some states have state-level net neutrality laws\n\nEuropean Union:\n- Established net neutrality regulations in 2016\n- Strong protections for internet users\n\nCanada:\n- Net neutrality principles are legally enforced\n\nBrazil:\n- Net neutrality laws exist but implementation is complex\n\nIndia:\n- Strong net neutrality regulations since 2018\n\nChina:\n- No net neutrality; heavy internet regulation\n\nRussia:\n- Limited net neutrality protections\n- Significant internet control\n\nJapan:\n- Supports net neutrality principles\n\nUnited Kingdom:\n- Follows EU net neutrality rules post-Brexit\n\nMany developing countries:\n- Lack comprehensive net neutrality regulations\n- Often limited by infrastructure and regulatory frameworks\n\nStatus is dynamic and subject to change, so current specifics might differ. Each country has unique approaches and implementation levels.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on net neutrality in a specific region or country?",
